definition:
A man living at the time of United Monarchy, first mentioned at 1Sa.27.2; 
 father of: Achish (H0397); also called Maacah (KJV: Maachah; NIV: Maakah) at 1Ki.2.39;
Another name of ma.okh (מָעוֹךְ "Maoch" H4582)
 § Maachah = "oppression"
 father of Achish, king of Gath at the beginning of Solomon's reign
